{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "A redundancy analysis was performed using a subset of 100,000 random k-mers sampled from the k-mer matrix of 920 Ae.",
    "tauschii accessions.",
    "The complete matrix contained 10,078,115,665 k-mers.",
    "The pairwise comparisons between accessions were performed by computing the sum of the presence-absence values (0 and 1) per k-mer between 2 accessions of the matrix.",
    "To determine the divergence, we computed the total number of 1 present in the summed string, each one corresponding to a difference in the presence/absence of the k-mer in the 2 compared accessions."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}